<p>SATISFY</p>
<p>satiare refers to the appeasing of a want generally, of hunger etc.</p>
<p>saturare refers to the appeasing of an unntural craving, or of an over-eager longing, e.g. a voracious hunger etc..</p>
<p/>
<p>SATISFIED</p>
<p>satis habere is consider something as enough and refers to a typically unempassioned judgment that one has no further claims or wishes in a certain situation.</p>
<p>contentum esse refers to the feeling of being satisfied and is typically a sign of moderation and self-control.</p>
<p>boni consulere refers to an act of the will by which a person resigns himself and acquiesces as becomes a man, to what is inevitable.</p>
